article.headline: Iowa State 72, Idaho State 59
article.story:
AMES, Iowa (AP) -- Anne O'Neil scored 16 points and Megan
Ronhovde and Lisa Kriener both had 14, leading Iowa State to a
72-59 victory over Idaho State in the first round of the WNIT on
Wednesday night.

Kriener got the game's first basket on a layup and Iowa State
(16-14), making its first appearance in the WNIT, never trailed.
The Cyclones assured themselves of a winning record for the eighth
time in nine seasons and will host Miami of Ohio in a second-round
game Friday night.

Miami beat Xavier 77-65 Wednesday night.

Molly Hays of Missoula, Mont., led Idaho State (20-9), the
runner-up in the Big Sky Conference, with 17 points and was the
only Bengals' player in double figures.

Idaho State plays a similar style to Iowa State -- spreading the
floor and looking for 3-point shots. But with Iowa State switching
from its usual zone defense to man-to-man, Idaho State went just
6-for-28 from 3-point range and shot only 35.4 percent overall.

Iowa State, meanwhile, quickly built a lead with Ronhovde's
3-point shooting and crisp passes that got the ball to Kriener for
easy baskets inside.

Kriener was 7-for-10 from the field and grabbed eight rebounds.
Ronhovde hit her first three 3-point shots and finished 4-for-6
from behind the arc.

Lyndsey Medders and Ronhovde hit consecutive 3s to start a 10-2
run that stretched Iowa State's lead to 33-19, and another Ronhovde
3 made it 36-21. The Cyclones led by as many as 16 before Idaho
State drew to 43-35 on Annie Anderson's free throw with 39 seconds
left in the first half.

The Bengals had a chance to get closer but turned the ball over
and Medders scored on a driving layup with 2 seconds left in the
half to put Iowa State up 45-35.

Idaho State threatened once in the second half, pulling to 51-41
on baskets by Hays and Anderson. But O'Neil hit a jumper and
followed that with a 3-pointer, sparking a 9-3 run that put the
Cyclones back in control at 60-44.
